50|$|A lot of <b>moving</b> <b>iron</b> {{speakers}} have no damping. This {{means the}} moving member resonates freely in the audio band. This {{is bad news}} for sound quality, but introducing damping heavily reduces sensitivity. This was impractical in pre-war times when amplification was very expensive, so <b>moving</b> <b>iron</b> has a history of being used with no damping.|$|R
