50|$|An {{alternative}} {{design is}} the <b>moving</b> <b>iron</b> variation on <b>moving</b> magnet used by ADC, Grado, Stanton/Pickering 681 series, Ortofon OM and VMS series, and the MMC cartridge of Bang & Olufsen. In these units, the magnet itself sits behind the four coils and magnetises the cores {{of all four}} coils. The <b>moving</b> <b>iron</b> cross {{at the other end}} of the coils varies the gaps between itself and each of these cores, according to its movements. These variations lead to voltage variations as described above.|$|R
